cip.render.raytrace.background

Class ConstantColour

  • java.lang.Object
    • cip.render.raytrace.background.ConstantColour
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDynXmlObject, INamedObject, IRtBackground

    public class ConstantColour
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDynXmlObject, INamedObject, IRtBackground
    A constant colour background - the same colour in all directions.

    The constant colour background is specified as a node in an XML file as: 

         <DynamicallyLoadedObject class="cip.raytrace.background.ConstantColour" name="backgroundName">
       <colour RGBf_attributes/>
     </DynamicallyLoadedObject>
    where:
    colour or color The colour as specified by the RGBf_attributes which are described in RGBf.setValue(Element, boolean)

    Example of XML Specification

    The following specifies a gray constant colour background: 

         <DynamicallyLoadedObject class="cip.raytrace.background.ConstantColour" name="background">
       <colour rgb="0.25,0.25,0.25"/>
     </DynamicallyLoadedObject>
    Since:
    1.0

        Description copied from interface: IRtBackground

        Specified by:
        getColor in interface IRtBackground
        Parameters:
        rgb - The rgb of the background.
        ray - The ray directed into the background. This may be null in which case a non-directional "average" background will be returned.
